l lymphomas.2</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/15/ALK-Protein_ALK-1" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','ALK Protein (ALK-1) on lymph node.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/15/ALK-Protein_ALK-1','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_204M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-15-alk-protein-alk-1-58D78086',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','CM/15/ALK-Protein_ALK-1');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS_STAGING (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7537','Villin',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>CWWB1</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Gastrointestinal (GI) Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>cytoplasmic, membranous</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>colon</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Villin is an actin-binding glycoprotein that serves an important role in the maintenance of of the microvilli brush border in gastrointestinal (GI) mucosal epithelium and its associated tumors.1,2Recent immunohistochemical studies with villin have shown that villin is not only expressed in carcinomas of the gastrointestinal tract, but also in renal cell carcinomas, pancreatic carcinomas, endometrial carcinomas, as well as carcinomas of the ovary and lungs.2In addition, positive villin expression may be seen in neuroendocrine/carcinoid tumors of the GI tract and lungs.3</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/150/Villin_CWWB1" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Small bowel mucosa is labelled by villin antibody in the spiral region.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/150/Villin_CWWB1','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_346M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-150-villin-cwwb1-02DA34FD',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','CM/150/Villin_CWWB1');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS_STAGING (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7538','Vimentin',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>V9</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Anatomic Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>cytoplasmic</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>tonsil, lymph node</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Vimentin is a 57kD, class-III, intermediate filament found in a variety of mesenchymal cells, including melanocytes, lymphocytes, endothelial cells, and fibroblasts. Non-reactivity of anti-vimentin is often considered more useful than its positive reactivity, since there are a few tumors that do not contain vimentin. The anti-vimentin immunohistochemical reagent is also useful as a tissue process control reagent.1-9</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/151/Vimentin_V9" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Lymphocyte/germinal center cells are labelled by vimentin antibody in the tonsil.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/151/Vimentin_V9','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_347M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-151-vimentin-v9-AF66A7C3',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','CM/151/Vimentin_V9');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS_STAGING (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7539','WT1',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>6F-H2</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Anatomic Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td></td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>Ovarian serous carcinoma (Nuclear); Mesothelioma (Nuclear); Kidney (Nuclear); Testis (Nuclear)</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Wilms’ tumor 1 protein (WT1) is a zinc finger transcription factor, normally expressed in tissues of mesodermal origin.1The Wilms’ tumor gene encodes a protein that functions as a tumor suppressor gene mapped to human chromosome 11p13.2Nuclear WT1 immunoreactivity has been observed in high frequencies in several types of mesoderm-derived tumors including epithelioid mesothelioma and ovarian serous carcinoma, and thus is used as a marker for these neoplasms.2,3,6</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/152/WT1_6F-H2" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Nuclear labelling of cells of mesothelioma by WT1 antibody.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/152/WT1_6F-H2','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_348M-9-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-152-wt1-6f-h2-723A279B',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','CM/152/WT1_6F-H2');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS_STAGING (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7541','BCA-225',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>Cu-18</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Anatomic Pathology • Breast/Gynecological Pathology • Cytopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>cytoplasmic</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>breast carcinoma</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:25-1:100*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Anti-BCA-225 primary antibody labels breast cancer antigen 225 (BCA-225) in primary and metastatic breast carcinoma. BCA-225 was first identified in T47D breast carcinoma cells, but its expression in other carcinomas such as lung, kidney, ovary and endometrium has also been demonstrated.1-4BCA-225 expression has also been found in sebaceous gland tumors.5,6</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/17/BCA-225_Cu-18" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','BCA-225 antibody shows a moderate to strong cytoplasmic staining reaction for breast invasive ductal carcinoma, metastatic to lymph node.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/17/BCA-225_Cu-18','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_225M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-17-bca-225-cu-18-C15F1416',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','CM/17/BCA-225_Cu-18');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS_STAGING (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7520','PAX-5',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>24</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Hematopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>nuclear</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>tonsil</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">PAX-5 encodes for B-cell-specific activator protein (BSAP), a marker for B-cells, including B-lymphoblastic neoplasms and maturation stage. It is found in most cases of mature and precursor B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphomas/leukemias. In approximately 97% of cases of classic Hodgkin lymphoma, Reed-Sternberg cells express PAX-5.4PAX-5 is not detected in multiple myeloma and solitary plasmacytoma, making it useful for such differentiation.1,3Diffuse large B-cell lymphomas do express PAX-5, save for those with terminal B-cell differentiation. T-cell neoplasms do not stain with anti-PAX-5. There is a strong association with CD20 expression.1-4</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/130/PAX-5_24" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Nuclear labelling of germinal center and mantle zone cells by PAX-5 antibody on adenoidal tissue.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/130/PAX-5_24','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_312M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-130-pax-5-24-B1C6B8A0',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','CM/130/PAX-5_24');
